<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05033g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05033g">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05033g"> 33(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> objecting bishop &mdash; Defensor</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">They and all the assembled bishops &mdash; with the exception of one &mdash; who were met to assist at the election, insisted on his consecration. <mark>The objecting bishop, whose name was Defensor</mark> (or Defender), in vain said tauntingly, &lsquo;Look, only look at him! his commonness! his soiled garments! the absurd cut of his hair!&rsquo; <small> Margaret Maitland, <a name="MMLL" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#MMLL"><cite title="source">Life and Legends of St. Martin of Tours (316-397)</cite></a> (1908) 40</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: A footnote in the text explains that &ldquo;in our modern Bibles, the word is Avenger, not Defender.&rdquo; (MT 41n) </mm> </dd></dl>
